{
  "stem": "1363.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now by that time, a lot of them lost faith and strength, mostly the older ones and the sick ones.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And as we were walking, by that time, we had some German soldiers or not Wehrmacht, but either SS or TOTs who were walking with us.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they had, of course, the guns.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And whoever could not walk and sat down, they shot them on the highway.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now they shot them, and they covered them with some sort of paper, newspaper, brown paper, whatever they could find in the vicinity.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Now at that time, I knew grandma had some gold coins.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were called Napoleon.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, gave me gold coins.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I had a pair of-- I had two pants, one on top of each other.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One was along within elastic on the bottom-- a rower, my uncle was a rower, professor rower, or hobby rower, or whatever.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he had sort of a drill material pair of trousers with elastic in the waist.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And underneath that I had a culotte.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the culotte was stitched in the center, double that there was a little hole, a strip going up to my waist.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we stuffed the Napoleon in there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And Napoleon was like our, 6-- 5 cents now.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But it was gold.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it was quite thick.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Now that gold coin was quite valuable at those days.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And people, they meant to kill for a Napoleon.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were French Napoleon money, which people somehow converted from the Hungarian money, which was not worth a pinch of salt, into Napoleon, because the gold was valuable.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I don't know how my grandma got them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Most probably that uncle who was well-to-do gave her some to survive, to try to rescue the children with that.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
